Preconditions:
The input list `piles` must not be null.
The input list `piles` must not be empty.
The input integer `k` must be greater than or equal to zero.
The length of each sublist in `piles` must be greater than or equal to `k`.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the maximum total value of coins.
The returned value should be greater than or equal to zero.
The returned value should be the maximum possible value of coins that can be obtained by choosing exactly `k` coins optimally.
The order of the piles in the input list `piles` should not be changed.
The order of the integers within each sublist in `piles` should not be changed.